Japan’s June LNG Imports Rise 11%; Crude Oil Purchases Gain 1.9%

-- B y   Y u j i   O k a d a
-- 
2011-07-21T04:01:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/japan-s-june-lng-imports-rise-11-crude-oil-purchases-gain-1-9-.html
Japan ’s liquefied natural gas
imports climbed 11 percent to 6.23 million metric tons from a
year earlier in June, the  Finance Ministry  said in a preliminary
trade report released in Tokyo today.  Imports of crude oil gained 1.9 percent to about 15.4
million kiloliters in the month. Japanese utilities used about
31 percent more LNG in June as they increased thermal generation
after closures of nuclear stations due to the March 11
earthquake and tsunami.  The following table shows Japan’s imports for June:  To contact the reporter on this story:
